  "prompt": "What is the meaning of \"Stand Up India\" in the scheme \"Stand Up India, Start Up India\"?",
  "response": "The \"Stand Up India\" scheme is an initiative launched by the Government of India aimed at promoting entrepreneurship among women and Scheduled Castes (SC) and Scheduled Tribes (ST) communities. It is part of the broader \"Stand Up India, Start Up India\" campaign, which seeks to foster innovation, entrepreneurship, and economic growth in the country.\n\nSpecifically, the \"Stand Up India\" scheme focuses on providing financial support to women and individuals from SC/ST communities who wish to start their own enterprises. The key features of the scheme include:\n\n1. **Loan Provision**: The scheme offers bank loans ranging from \u20b910 lakh to \u20b91 crore to at least one entrepreneur from the SC/ST category and one woman entrepreneur per bank branch for setting up a greenfield enterprise. The enterprise could be in the manufacturing, services, or trading sector.\n\n2. **Greenfield Project**: The loan is intended for new, innovative, or scalable projects that are being set up for the first time.\n\n3. **Comprehensive Support**: The scheme provides not only financial assistance but also support in the form of capacity building, handholding, and mentoring to ensure the success of the entrepreneurs.\n\n4. **Better Interest Rate**: The loans are provided at a lower interest rate, which makes it easier for entrepreneurs to repay the loan while still growing their businesses.\n\nThe \"Stand Up India\" scheme is designed to address the challenges faced by marginalized sections of society in accessing credit and other resources necessary to start and run a business. By empowering women and SC/ST entrepreneurs, the scheme aims to create a more inclusive and equitable economic environment, leading to job creation and overall economic development.",
